Anonymous Sun 17 Feb 2019 19:14:55 No.21357717 Report
Quoted By: >>21358275
Hey Durr, wanted to give you some feedback since I doubt anyone really bothers.

1) Everything you write feels like you're doing it in a hurry. Slow down, take your time, and think about what you're writing. It doesn't need to be rushed.

2) Out of Place has an entire section that is literally a copy and paste of the previous section, but with the added perspective of a third party. Ask yourself: would anything have suffered if you had just included the added perspective in the first place? No one is going to read the same thing a second time, they're just going to skim through it.

3) The part with Krystal and her "needs" is really out of nowhere and disrupts the tone of everything, as does the resolution. And everyone is just fine with it, NBD. Really jarring.

4) You can make the main character awesome without making him the undisputed king of the universe who knows all the cool kids. Let him have some flaws, it makes him more relatable.
